## Superseded: ci-matrix-fail-fast-iterative-fix

```yaml
name: ci-matrix-fail-fast-iterative-fix
description: "In a GitHub Actions matrix with default fail-fast: true, when one entry FAILS the siblings get CANCELLED before their own steps run — hiding their latent failures. Fix the failing entry first, push, and let CI surface what the siblings actually do."
category: ci-cd
date: 2026-05-16
version: "1.0.0"
user-invocable: false
verification: verified-local
```

Verified on AchaeanFleet PR #662 (6-vessel Build Vessel Images matrix, 1 FAILURE + 5 CANCELLED).

---

